str2: All, the whole, every kind of. Including all the forms of declension; apparently a primary word; all, any, every, the whole.

parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Plural
str2: Properly, to stare at, i.e. to discern clearly; by extension, to attend to; by Hebraism, to experience; passively, to appear.

parse: Verb - Imperfect Indicative Active - 3rd Person Plural
str2: To murmur greatly, continue murmuring. From dia and gogguzo; to complain throughout a crowd.

parse: Verb - Present Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Plural
str2: (a) I say, speak; I mean, mention, tell, (b) I call, name, especially in the pass., (c) I tell, command.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To go in, come in, enter. From eis and erchomai; to enter.
From kata and luo; to loosen down, i.e. to demolish; specially to halt for the night.
Gen: from; dat: beside, in the presence of; acc: alongside of.
Sinning, sinful, depraved, detestable. From hamartano; sinful, i.e. A sinner.
A male human being; a man, husband. A primary word; a man.
